  "message": "Update RaptorQ wavefront pipeline benchmark timings\n\nRe-ran the Track F wavefront pipeline benchmark suite (20 samples per\nconfiguration). Key changes in timing data:\n\n- Batch-4 wavefront delta vs sequential narrowed from -12.0% to -3.2%\n- Batch-8 wavefront delta narrowed from -11.4% to -1.8%\n- Batch-16 wavefront delta narrowed from -11.7% to -4.1%\n- Sequential p95 dropped from 49235us to 42923us (improved baseline)\n- Wavefront p95 values tightened across all batch sizes\n\nThe narrower deltas reflect the improved sequential baseline rather than\nwavefront regression \u2014 absolute wavefront times are comparable or slightly\nbetter. Wavefront batch/overlap counts unchanged, confirming the pipeline\nstructure is stable.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
